The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 12 June is 42,663 (4,938 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 07 June, there were 256 new confirmed cases (29.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 31 May, there were 137 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 87% (119 extra cases).
